      <comment>Updated list</comment>
      <text xml:space="preserve">{{sabermetric | formula = &lt;math&gt;TB = 1B + 2(2B) + 3(3B) + 4 (HR)&lt;/math&gt;}}

In [[baseball statistics]], '''total bases''' refers to the number of bases a player has gained with [[hit (baseball)|hits]], i.e., the sum of his hits [[weight function|weighted]] by 1 for a [[single (baseball)|single]], 2 for a [[double (baseball)|double]], 3 for a [[triple (baseball)|triple]] and 4 for a [[home run]].
Only bases attained from [[Hit (baseball)|hits]] count toward this total. 


