    <title>Games played</title>
    <id>3814</id>
    <revision>
      <id>422286892</id>
      <timestamp>2011-04-04T09:08:05Z</timestamp>
      <contributor>
        <username>Yobot</username>
        <id>7328338</id>
      </contributor>
      <minor />
      <comment>[[WP:CHECKWIKI]] error 61 fixes + [[WP:GENFIXES|general fixes]], References after punctuation per [[WP:REFPUNC]] and [[WP:PAIC]] using [[Project:AWB|AWB]] (7671)</comment>
      <text xml:space="preserve">'''Games played''' (most often abbreviated as '''G''' or '''GP''') is a [[statistic]] used in [[team sports]] to indicate the total number of games in which a player has participated (in any capacity); the statistic is generally applied irrespective of whatever portion of the game is contested.

==Baseball==
In [[baseball]], the [[baseball statistics|statistic]] applies also to players who, prior to a game, are included on a [[starting lineup]] card or are announced as ''ex ante'' substitutes, whether they actually play or not,&lt;ref&gt;[http://mlb.mlb.com/mlb/official_info/official_rules/official_scorer_10.jsp Section 20 of the official scorer guidelines]&lt;/ref&gt; although, in [[Major League Baseball]], the application of this statistic does not extend to consecutive games played streaks.

A [[starting pitcher]], then, may be credited with a game played even as he is not credited with a [[games started|game started]], an [[innings pitched|inning pitched]], or a [[complete game]].

==See also==
*[[Major League Baseball consecutive games played streaks]]

