      <comment>no need for this (or at least, provide a complete table)</comment>
      <text xml:space="preserve">{{unreferenced|date=June 2009|bot=yes}}
[[Image:Baseballpositions.png|280px|right]]
There are 9 '''fielding positions''' in [[baseball]]. Each [[Baseball scorekeeping#Defensive positions|position]] conventionally has an associated number (from 1 to 9) which is used [[official scorer|to score]] [[putout]]s.  For example:
*If the third baseman fields a ball and throws it to first, it is recorded as a 5–3 [[out (baseball)|out]].
*A [[double play]] where the second baseman fields, throws to the shortstop covering second base, who throws to the 1st baseman is recorded as a 4–6–3 double play.

The fielding positions in baseball are the basis for the famous comedy routine ''[[Who's On First?]]'', created by the team of [[Abbott and Costello]].

