| Boston becomes the first baseball team in history to win a series after losing the first three games. The series featured, among other things, two consecutive postseason blown saves by [[New York Yankees|Yankee]] closer [[Mariano Rivera]] and two consecutive game winning hits from [[Red Sox]] slugger [[David Ortiz]] in Games 4 and 5. The Red Sox' first pennant since [[1986 American League Championship Series|1986]]. The Red Sox, who had been three outs away from elimination in Game 4, tied the game in the bottom of the ninth inning, won it in the 12th, won the next three games in a rematch of the previous year's ALCS and went on to win the World Series for the first time in 86 years.
