|WP=[[Bill Dinneen]] (1–0)|LP=[[Sam Leever]] (0–1)|SV=
|RoadHR=|HomeHR=[[Patsy Dougherty]] 2 (2)
|}}

===Game 3===
Saturday, October 3, 1903 at [[Huntington Avenue Grounds|Huntington Avenue Baseball Grounds]] in [[Boston]], [[Massachusetts]]

Deacon Phillippe, pitching on only one day rest, started Game 3 for the Pirates, and did not let them down as he pitched his second complete game victory of the series to put the Pirates up two games to one.

{{Linescore|
|Road='''Pittsburgh'''|RoadAbr=PIT
|R1=0|R2=1|R3=2|R4=0|R5=0|R6=0|R7=0|R8=1|R9=0|RR=4|RH=7|RE=1
